docs.abstract: The Avenue des Champs-Élysées, built for royalty and named after paradise, has become crowded with fast food, fast fashion and fast scooters. The city hopes to change that.

docs.lead_paragraph: PARIS — The sidewalks are cracked along “la plus belle avenue du monde” — the most beautiful street in the world. Each day, 60,000 cars clog the lanes. Walkways are cluttered with abandoned scooters.
